🛠️ Tech Stack

Python 3.11+

Streamlit

scikit-learn
 (TF-IDF, NearestNeighbors)

SentenceTransformers
 (semantic embeddings)

pdfplumber
 (PDF text extraction)

python-docx
 (Word file support)

📂 Project Structure
deep_researcher_agent/
│
├── main.py                # CLI entry point
├── streamlit_app.py       # Streamlit entry point (for hosting)
├── requirements.txt       # dependencies
├── data/                  # sample docs + uploaded files
│   └── uploads/           # user-uploaded docs (ephemeral in cloud)
├── exports/               # embeddings + metadata (rebuilt each run)
└── src/
    ├── ingest_and_chunk.py    # ingestion + chunking
    ├── embed_index.py         # embeddings + index
    ├── retrieve.py            # retrieval wrapper
    ├── reasoning.py           # query decomposition
    ├── synthesize.py          # summarization + export
    └── app_streamlit.py       # Streamlit UI

⚡ Quick Start (Local)
# 1. Clone repo
git clone https://github.com/your-username/deep-researcher-agent.git
cd deep-researcher-agent

# 2. Create virtual env
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate   # (Windows)
# or source venv/bin/activate (Linux/Mac)

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Run Streamlit UI
streamlit run src/app_streamlit.py

# 5. (Optional) Run CLI
python main.py

🚀 Deploy (Streamlit Cloud)

Fork this repo.

Connect to Streamlit Cloud
.

Deploy streamlit_app.py as the entry point.

App builds automatically on each commit.

